[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/stardewvalley/mods/10668?tab=description]Enchantable Scythes And Golden Scythe Respawns[/url] or [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/stardewvalley/mods/26217?tab=description]Scythe Tool Enchantments[/url] (don't use both together)[/*]
[*]Should be compatible with new enchantment and new ring mods as long as they are using [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/stardewvalley/mods/2400]SMAPI [/url]to properly add them.[/*]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/stardewvalley/mods/46822?tab=description]JP's Wear More Trinkets[/url][/*]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/stardewvalley/mods/15933]Napalm Mummies[/url] - works out of the box: this mod ships a built-in patch so Napalm Rings in extra slots (or nested deep in combined rings) still detonate crumpled mummies.[/*]
[*]Compatible with [url=http://forums.stardewvalley.net/threads/unofficial-mod-updates.2096/post-173170]chiccenDev's More Rings 1.2.4[/url] (the 1.6-compatible Content Patcher version). The patch is optional and self-disabling: it does nothing if More Rings isn't installed.
[list]
[*][i]Note: Some More Rings effects apply once regardless of count - Wide Nets and Far Reaching - and True Sight / Diamond Booze are on/off effects. That's More Rings' own behavior, the same in any ring slot.[/i][/*]
[/list]
[/*]
[*]Ships with translations for all 11 supported languages (German, Spanish, French, Hungarian, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Portuguese, Russian, Turkish, Chinese). Machine-assisted - corrections welcome![/*]
[*]Android is likely NOT compatible.[/*]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/stardewvalley/mods/3214]Wear More Rings[/url] is NOT compatible[/*]
[/list]

[line]

[size=4][b]✦ Installation[/b][/size]

[list=1]
[*]Install [url=https://smapi.io]SMAPI[/url] 4.0 or later.[/*]
[*]Download this mod and unzip it into [i]Stardew Valley/Mods[/i] or download with Vortex.[/*]
[*]Run the game once with SMAPI to generate [i]config.json[/i].[/*]
[*]Optional: install [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/stardewvalley/mods/5098]Generic Mod Config Menu[/url]
to configure in-game.[/*]
[/list]

[line]

[size=4][b]✦ Uninstalling[/b][/size]

Before removing this mod, return your extra-slot rings to your inventory.  You have three options:

[list=1]
[*]Open the inventory menu, drag every extra ring back to your bag yourself.[/*]
[*]Open Generic Mod Config Menu → Multi Ring Infinite Forging → toggle "[b]Eject all extra rings now[/b]" and apply.[/*]
[*]In the SMAPI console, type [i]mrif_drain[/i] and press Enter.[/*]
[/list]

Then save and quit.  Rings still in extra slots when the mod is removed remain in the save file but are unreachable until the mod is reinstalled - at which point they'll reappear in the extra slot panel.

[b]Recovery if you forgot:[/b] reinstall the mod, load your save, run [i]mrif_drain[/i] in the console, save, and uninstall again.

[line]

[size=4][b]✦ Bug reports[/b][/size]

If something doesn't work as expected:

[list=1]
[*]Reproduce the issue once with [b]Verbose Logging[/b] enabled in the mod config.[/*]
[*]Attach your [i]SMAPI-latest.txt[/i] (found in[i] StardewValley/ErrorLogs/[/i] or via the SMAPI log parser at [url=https://smapi.io/log]smapi.io/log[/url]).[/*]
[*]Include a short description of the steps you took and what you expected to happen.[/*]
[/list]

